column73:
We are developing a smartphone app with two subscription levels.The free monitoring plan enables one user within bluetooth range of the wearable health device to visualize real-time values for heart rate, body temperature, and body orientation. The premium monitoring plan enable multiple users to view all features in the free monitoring plan plus it utilizes personalized analytics to provide real-time notifications to abnormal values and trends for each individual, historical trends, alert history, monthly reports, and the ability to share data with other caregivers including your physician.

column87: Charging for alerts to abnormal conditions, when especially in the chronically ill a spike in heart rate or a fall may be life-threatening, is deeply immoral. While the free app functions may be beneficial, I would choose to not to buy into a service that is predatory on nature. There is not currently an affordable monitor like this, and the potential is very exciting. The idea of having to pay in order to take it from "novelty self-study" to "medically useful" is abhorrent.
